Meanings":[{"name":"Eccles","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Eccles in Lancashire, or possibly from any of several other places so named in Kent, Norfolk, Berwickshire, and Dumfriesshire, from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’). Such places would have been the sites of notable pre-Anglo-Saxon churches or Christian places of communal worship."],"variants":[{"name":"Ackles","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles  ."]},{"name":"Exley","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): habitational name from Exley in Southowram (Yorkshire), from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Compare   Eccles  .","Americanized form of South German   Oechsle  ."]},{"name":"Echols","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles   and possibly also of German   Eckels  ."]},{"name":"Eckles","meanings":["English: variant of   Eccles  . This form is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Eccles was born in 1226, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 daughters with Alexander de Denton. She died in 1268, in Denton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1226–1268":"1226–1268","1215–1285":"1215–1285","1240–1310":"1240–1310","1242–1299":"1242–1299","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1268":"1268","1299":"1299","1310":"1310","Abt 1242":"umbes 1242","1242":"1242","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England",",Cheshire,England.":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Denton,Lancashire,England.":"Denton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1226–1268":"1226–1268","1215–1285":"1215–1285","1240–1310":"1240–1310","1242–1299":"1242–1299","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1268":"1268","1299":"1299","1310":"1310","Abt 1242":"noin 1242","1242":"1242","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England",",Cheshire,England.":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Denton,Lancashire,England.":"Denton, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1226–1268":"1226–1268","1215–1285":"1215–1285","1240–1310":"1240–1310","1242–1299":"1242–1299","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1268":"1268","1299":"1299","1310":"1310","Abt 1242":"environ 1242","1242":"1242","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, Angleterre",",Cheshire,England.":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Denton,Lancashire,England.":"Denton, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alice Eccles est née en 1226, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 filles avec Alexander de Denton. Elle est décédée en 1268, à Denton, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 42 ans."},"de":{"1226–1268":"1226–1268","1215–1285":"1215–1285","1240–1310":"1240–1310","1242–1299":"1242–1